 drama films]]\n[[Category:Russian films]]\n[[Category:Russian-language films]]\n[[Category:Russian drama films]]\n{{Russia-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2012 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Betrayal\n| image          = Betrayal (2012 film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Kirill Serebrennikov]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Franziska Petri]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2012|08|29|[[69th Venice International Film Festival|Venice]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 115 minutes\n| country        = Russia\n| language       = Russian\n}}\n'''''Betrayal''''' ({{lang-ru|\u0418\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0430|Izmena}}) is a 2012 Russian [[drama film]] directed by [[Kirill Serebrennikov]]. The film was selected to compete for the [[Golden Lion]] at the [[69th Venice International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"labiennale\">{{cite web |url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/festival/lineup/off-sel/venezia69/ |title=Venezia 69 |accessdate=4 August 2012 |work=labiennale |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728223053/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/festival/lineup/off-sel/venezia69 |archive-date=28 July 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> At the 2012 [[Abu Dhabi Film Festival]], Franziska Petri won the award for Best Actress.<ref name=\"Abu Dhabi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abudhabifilmfestival.ae/en/program/awards |title=2012 Awards |accessdate=28 October 2012 |work=Abu Dhabi Film Festival}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nTwo random acquaintances learn that their spouses are lovers. This discovery makes them act in a way they would not have dared earlier.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Albina Dzhanabaeva]]\n* [[Dejan Lilic]]\n* [[Franziska Petri]]\n* [[Art\u016brs Skrasti\u0146\u0161]]\n* [[Svetlana Mamresheva]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2299954|Betr