{"title_page": "High Schools (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1984 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = High Schools\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Charles Guggenheim]]\n| producer       = Charles Guggenheim<br>Nancy Sloss\n| writer         = \n| narrator       = \n| starring       = \n| music          = \n| cinematography = Wayne Ewing\n| editing        = [[Jay Cassidy]]\n| studio         = Guggenheim Productions\n| distributor    = [[Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of Teaching]] and [[WETA-TV|WETA]]\n| released       = {{film date|1984}}\n| runtime        = 28 minutes\n| country        = United States \n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''High Schools''''' is a 1984 American [[documentary film]] produced and directed by [[Charles Guggenheim]]. It is based on [[Ernest L. Boyer]]'s book, ''High School'', and was filmed on location in seven American high schools.<ref name=gpi>{{cite web |title=Filmography |publisher=Guggenheim Productions, Inc. |url=http://www.gpifilms.com/filmography.html}}</ref> The film was nominated for an [[Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300493/Highschools/details |title= High Schools |accessdate=November 16, 2008|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0087409|title=High Schools}}\n*[http://www.gpifilms.com/orders.html Guggenheim Productions, Inc. website].\n\n{{Charles Guggenheim |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:High Schools}}\n[[Category:1984 films]]\n[[Category:1980s documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about high school in the United States]]\n\n\n{{bio-documentary-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1984 film}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = High Schools\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Charles Guggenheim]]\n| producer       = Charles Guggenheim<br>Nancy Sloss\n| writer         = \n| narrator       = \n| starring       = \n| music          = \n| cinematography = Wayne Ewing\n| editing        = [[Jay Cassidy]]\n| studio         = Guggenheim Productions\n| distributor    = [[Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of Teaching]] and [[WETA-TV|WETA]]\n| released       = {{film date|1984}}\n| runtime        = 28 minutes\n| country        = United States \n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''High Schools''''' is a 1984 American [[documentary film]] produced and directed by [[Charles Guggenheim]]. It is based on [[Ernest L. Boyer]]'s book, ''High School'', and was filmed on location in seven American high schools.<ref name=gpi>{{cite web |title=Filmography |publisher=Guggenheim Productions, Inc. |url=http://www.gpifilms.com/filmography.html}}</ref> The film was nominated for an [[Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300493/Highschools/details |title= High Schools |accessdate=November 16, 2008|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0087409|title=High Schools}}\n*[http://www.gpifilms.com/orders.html Guggenheim Productions, Inc. website].\n\n{{Charles Guggenheim |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:High Schools}}\n[[Category:1984 films]]\n[[Category:1980s documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about high school in the United States]]\n\n\n{{bio-documentary-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_Schools_(film)"}
